==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Renard
<hw>Ren"ard</hw> <pr>(r?n"?rd)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>renard</ets> the fox, the name of the fox in a celebrated epic
poem, and of German origin, G. <ets>Reinhard</ets>, OHG.
<ets>Reginhard</ets>, properly, strong in counsel; <ets>regin</ets>
counsel (akin to Goth. <ets>ragin</ets>) + <ets>hart</ets> hard. See
<er>Hard</er>.]</ety> <def>A fox; -- so called in fables or familiar
tales, and in poetry.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>reynard</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Renardine</ent>⟦br⟧
